The answer is : The ALOHA (No HLA-OG) model demonstrates the largest performance improvement over other models, scoring the highest in most metrics like Hits@1/20, Hits@5/20, and Hits@10/20. It has a higher mean rank than other models except for the Uniform model, which is a bit higher, and the bi-ranker model, which is much higher. Despite having lower MRR, the model still outperforms others in most of the metrics.
